t, England":"Tunbridge, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Grays (Thurrock), Essex, England":"Grays, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Thurrock Grey, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Clare","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish (Clare, Wicklow, and Wexford): habitational name from Clare in Suffolk (an eastern county of England), the center of a major Norman baronial estate since the Norman Conquest. The English placename probably originated as a Celtic river name meaning ‘bright, gentle, or warm’. The surname is not from the Irish county name <i>Clare</i>, which is either from the surname or from a place called with Gaelic <i>clár</i> ‘plank bridge’. Another Norman surname in the southeast of Ireland was <i>de Clere</i>, from Clères in Seine-Maritime (France), named from the local river.","English and French: from the Middle English, Old French female personal name <i>Cla(i)re</i> (from Latin <i>Clara</i>, from <i>clarus</i> ‘clear, bright, famous’) which achieved some popularity, greater elsewhere in Europe than in England, through the fame of Saint Clare of Assisi (see   Chiara  ). The English surname seems to have been interchangeable with   Clear   1.","English: occupational name from an agent derivative of Middle English <i>cley</i> ‘clay’. The work of medieval clayers involved plastering a framework of interwoven twigs with mud to produce wattle-and-daub work."],"variants":[{"name":"Claire","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Clare  .","Variant of   Clair  , an altered form of German   Klare  .","French: variant of   Clair  ."]},{"name":"Chiara","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Marco, Amedeo, Angelo, Gino, Rocco.","Italian: from the female personal name <i>Chiara</i> or <i>Clara</i>, a name popularized in the medieval period by the cult of Saint Clare of Assisi (<i>c.</i> 1193–1253); she was an associate of Saint Francis of Assisi and founded the order of nuns known as the Poor Clares. See also   Chiaro  ."]},{"name":"Claar","meanings":["German: variant of <b>Klaar</b> (and, in North America, an altered form of this), a nickname from Middle High German, Middle Low German <i>klar</i> ‘pure, pretty, sensible’, or a habitational name from a minor place so named near Braunschweig.","Possibly also an Americanized form of Dutch <b>Klaar</b>: from a vernacular form of the female personal name <i>Clara</i> (see   Clare   2)."]},{"name":"Clarkin","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cheshire): from a pet form of the personal name <i>Clare</i> (compare   Clare   and   Clear  ), which is both a masculine and a female personal name in Middle English.","Irish (Monaghan): variant of   Clerkin  ."]},{"name":"Clear","meanings":["English (southeastern England, of Norman origin): from <i>Clere</i>, the French popular form of the personal name   Clare   2, and possibly interchangeable with it or confused with it.","English (southeastern): probably a habitational name from clere, a component of several placenames in north Hampshire (Highclere, Burghclere, Kingsclere). This is probably from a Celtic stream name meaning ‘bright’ (cognate with Latin <i>clarus</i> ‘clear, bright’).","Americanized form (translation into English) of German   Klar   1."]}]},{"name":"Elana","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Late Latin.  See  <b>Éliane</b>   ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Elana de Clare was born in 1153, in Tunbridge, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Lord Thurrock John De Grey Sir. She died in 1184, in Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1153–1184":"1153–1184","1158–1198":"1158–1198","1176–1219":"1176–1219","1158":"1158","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1153":"1153","1184":"1184","1219":"1219","Tunbridge Castle, Kent, England":"Tunbridge, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Grays (Thurrock), Essex, England":"Grays, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thurrock Grey, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1153–1184":"1153–1184","1158–1198":"1158–1198","1176–1219":"1176–1219","1158":"1158","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1153":"1153","1184":"1184","1219":"1219","Tunbridge Castle, Kent, England":"Tunbridge, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Grays (Thurrock), Essex, England":"Grays, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Thurrock Grey, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1153–1184":"1153–1184","1158–1198":"1158–1198","1176–1219":"1176–1219","1158":"1158","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1153":"1153","1184":"1184","1219":"1219","Tunbridge Castle, Kent, England":"Tunbridge, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Grays (Thurrock), Essex, England":"Grays, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Thurrock Grey, Essex, England":"Thurrock, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elana de Clare est née en 1153, à Tunbridge, Kent, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Lord Thurrock John De Grey Sir. Elle est décédée en 1184, à Buckingham, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 31 ans."},"de":{"1153–1184":"1153–1184","1158–1198":"1158–1198","1176–1219":"1176–1219","1158":"1158","1176":"1176","1198":"1198","1153":"1153","1184":"1184","1219":"1219","Tunbridge Castle, Kent, England":"Tunbridge, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Grays (Thurrock), Essex, England":"Grays, Essex, England, United Ki